The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks for time series data, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). The paper also discusses the pre-processing of raw data, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of spectrogram and mel-spectrogram coefficients as input to the neural network suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of adaptive filters and their influence on learning success, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
